Now that we've been trapped at home with our kids for the past couple of weeks, I feel the urge to share this letter board post. It makes me giggle every time I see it because there's no such thing as relaxing when you're a parent. And now that we've been juggling parenting, working, keeping up with house chores and whatnot, there's ABSOLUTELY zero relaxing happening. But although it's tough as hell, I wouldn't have it any other way. I know I won't get to spend this much time with Luna ever again. So I try to remind myself of that every single day.
